4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE GENERATION
5 OF ENERGY AND TRANSMISSION OF ELECTRICITY; ESTABLISHING A STATE ENERGY AUTHORITY;
6 PROVIDING THE AUTHORITY WITH CERTAIN POWERS; REQUIRING THAT STATE AGENCIES
7 COOPERATE WITH THE AUTHORITY; CREATING A SPECIAL REVENUE ACCOUNT; STATUTORILY
8 APPROPRIATING MONEY FROM THE WHOLESALE ENERGY TRANSACTION TAX TO THE AUTHORITY
9 TO SUPPORT ITS ACTIVITIES; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; PROVIDING A STATUTORY APPROPRIATION;
10 AMENDING SECTIONS 15-72-106 AND 17-7-502, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 through 10] may be cited as the "Montana Energy
15 Authority Act".
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Purpose. The legislature finds and declares that:
18 (1) Montana is endowed with significant and diverse energy resources. The development of
19 Montana's energy resources is essential to a healthy state economy.
20 (2) Montana's energy resources provide a tremendous opportunity to diversify the state's economy
21 and to stabilize and increase revenue to the state;
22 (3) Energy generation and electric transmission constraints impede the development of the state's
23 energy resources;
24 (4) an essential function of government and its public purpose is to assist with the removal of
25 energy generation and electric transmission impediments to facilitate the development of Montana's energy
26 resources;
27 (5) development of Montana's energy resources promotes the public interest by increasing
28 employment, stimulating economic activity, augmenting sources of tax revenue, fostering economic stability,
