2 (iii) six members appointed to 3-year terms.
3 (5) In selecting the members, the governor shall:
4 (a) consider each prospective member's knowledge and understanding of the structural and
5 financial dimensions of the energy generation and electric transmission components of the state's economy;
6 (b) ensure that six members broadly represent, as evidenced by their background, experience,
7 and livelihood, the following categories of energy consumption:
8 (i) residential;
9 (ii) agricultural; and
10 (iii) commercial and industrial enterprise;
11 (c) choose two members with experience in electric transmission, distribution, and energy
12 generation issues; and
13 (d) choose two members with experience in renewable energy.
14 (6) The membership of the authority must include the following four members appointed by the
15 governor:
16 (i) a representative of the department of commerce;
17
18 (ii) a representative of the department of environmental quality;
19
20 (iii) a representative of the public service commission; and
21 (iv) a representative of the governor's office.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Compensation -- per diem. Members of the authority may not receive a
24 salary but are entitled to compensation as provided in 2-15-122 for each day they are engaged in the
25 transaction of official business. Members must be reimbursed for travel expenses, as provided in 2-18-501
26 through 2-18-503, incurred while on official business.
27
28 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Election of officers -- frequency of meetings -- quorum. (1) The
