1 members of the authority shall annually elect a presiding officer and a vice presiding officer from among the
2 authority membership. The presiding officer and vice presiding officer shall each serve a 1-year term.
3 (2) The authority shall meet at least every 90 days and at other times as called by the PRESIDING
4 OFFICER or by any SIX members of the authority.
5 (3) Eight members of the authority constitute a quorum for the transaction of all business, including
6 the election of officers.
