8 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Authority powers. The state energy authority may:
9 (1) facilitate the planning, development, economic analysis, and coordination of facilities within and
10 outside of the state;
11 (2) employ officers, agents, and employees that the authority considers necessary in carrying out
12 the provisions of [sections 1 through 10];
13 (3) contract for legal, financial, engineering, and other professional services necessary in carrying
14 out the provisions of [sections 1 through 10];
15 (4) receive by gift, grant, donation, or otherwise money, aid, or assistance from the federal
16 government, the state, any political subdivision, or any other public or private entity;
17 (5) assist in investigating, planning, establishing, and coordinating corridors for electric
18 transmission through all energy generating resource types;
19 (6) participate in regional energy transmission organizations established in response to or in
20 compliance with an order of the federal energy regulatory commission or any regional electric transmission
21 initiatives;
22 (7) participate in a regional organization established for the purpose of planning, analyzing, and
23 coordinating energy generation projects, electric transmission projects and transmission infrastructure;
24 (8) report any findings and recommendations as requested by the governor or the legislature; and
25 (9) perform other functions necessary to carry out the provisions of [sections 1 through 10].
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Interagency cooperation. (1) State agencies shall cooperate with the
28 authority in planning, permitting, and constructing facilities.
