4 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Administrative costs. (1) (a) The authority may be assessed costs by
5 the department, on request or pursuant to 2-15-121, for the services the department provides, including but not
6 limited to:
7 (i) personal services costs;
8
9 (ii) operating costs;
10
11 (iii) office and office equipment costs; and
12
13 (iv) other administrative costs.
14
15 (b) The costs charged must have a substantial relationship to the costs of services provided.
16 (2) The department shall provide an annual accounting to the authority of the incurred and indirect
17 costs that are attributable to the program.
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 10. Special revenue account -- statutory appropriation. (1) There is a
20 Montana energy generation and electric transmission special revenue account within the state special revenue
21 fund established in 17-2-102.
22 (2) (a) Money received from the wholesale energy transaction tax, as provided in 15-72-106, must
23 be deposited in the account.
24 (b) Money deposited in the account is statutorily appropriated, as provided in 17-7-502, to the
25 energy authority to meet the administrative costs of the authority.
